    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "Work-up": {
          "text": "Heterophile antibody (monospot) test vs EBV IgM Assay\nCBC\nLymphocytosis (≥50% lymphocytes)\n10% or more atypical lymphocytes\nHypersegmented neutrophils\nThrombocytopenia\nLFTs\nElevations in AST and ALT is expected up to 5x\nSuspected mononucleosis during pregnancy (also need to rule out other pathology):\nEpstein-Barr virus\n,\ncytomegalovirus\n, and\nHIV",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Diagnosis": {
          "text": "Heterophile antibody (monospot) test\nSensitivity of 87% and specificity of 91%\n[4]\nUp to 25% of patients in 1st week of symptoms may have false negative test\n[5]\n10% of adult patients with EBV infection will be persistently negative\nUp to 50% of pediatric patients will be persistently negative\n[6]\nEBV IgM Assay\nCarries 97% sensitivity and 94% specificity at symptom onset\n[7]",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
      "tables": [],
